translated_by_TA:
I was walking, my fists in my ripped pockets;
my overcoat was also becoming ideal;
I was walking under the sky, muse! and I was your vassal;
oh! there! what splendid loves I have dreamed of!
my only trousers had a large hole.
– dreamy little poucet, I scattered rhymes in my course;
my inn was under the big bear.
– my stars in the sky had a soft rustling sound
and I listened to them, sitting by the roadside,
those September evenings when I felt drops
of dew on my forehead, like a strengthening wine;
where, rhyming among the fantastical shadows,
like lyres, I plucked the elastic
of my injured shoes, one foot near my heart!
